BC-250 / Cyan Skillfish: EXPERIMENTAL memory/SDMA/NBIO clock gating

*** UNVALIDATED REGISTER MAPS — this layer can black-screen the box. ***

Applies ON TOP OF bc250-cg-flags.patch. Where that layer stays inside the
Navi10-validated GFX path, this one folds cyan skillfish's IP revisions
into a *different* revision's clock-gating register programming:

  MMHUB 2.0.3  -> grouped with mmhub_v2_0 2.0.0/2.0.2
  ATHUB 2.0.3  -> grouped with athub_v2_0 2.0.0/2.0.2
  SDMA  5.0.1  -> grouped with sdma_v5_0  5.0.0/5.0.2/5.0.5
  NBIF  2.1.1  -> routed into nv_common_set_clockgating_state (enables HDP)

None of these revisions is validated by AMD for that register map. The
strongest evidence they differ: AMD ships cyan skillfish its OWN SDMA
golden-settings table (golden_settings_sdma_cyan_skillfish in sdma_v5_0.c),
i.e. it treats 5.0.1's registers as distinct from the generic navi1x set —
yet this layer applies the generic CG programming to it anyway. The MC
(MMHUB/ATHUB) path is the most likely to hang: gating the memory hub on a
mismatched register map stalls VRAM/scanout -> black screen.

The cg_flags line here is an OR-append after external_rev_id, so this hunk
is independent of the GFX-layer cg_flags assignment (they touch different
lines and stack/reverse in any order). Every path is flag-gated, so bisect
at boot with amdgpu.cg_mask: start GFX-only (0x5), then add MC (bits 8/9),
SDMA (10/11), HDP (16/17) to find the offender. cg_mask=0 = stock behavior.

--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/nv.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/nv.c
@@ -874,6 +874,19 @@
 			AMD_CG_SUPPORT_GFX_CGCG;
 		adev->pg_flags = 0;
 		adev->external_rev_id = adev->rev_id + 0x82;
+		/* EXPERIMENTAL: unvalidated register maps for MC/SDMA/ATHUB/
+		 * HDP on cyan skillfish — bisect with amdgpu.cg_mask if the
+		 * display goes dark. See bc250-cg-flags-unvalidated.patch.
+		 */
+		adev->cg_flags |= AMD_CG_SUPPORT_IH_CG |
+			AMD_CG_SUPPORT_HDP_MGCG |
+			AMD_CG_SUPPORT_HDP_LS |
+			AMD_CG_SUPPORT_SDMA_MGCG |
+			AMD_CG_SUPPORT_SDMA_LS |
+			AMD_CG_SUPPORT_MC_MGCG |
+			AMD_CG_SUPPORT_MC_LS |
+			AMD_CG_SUPPORT_ATHUB_MGCG |
+			AMD_CG_SUPPORT_ATHUB_LS;
 		break;
 	case IP_VERSION(10, 3, 6):
 		adev->cg_flags = AMD_CG_SUPPORT_GFX_MGCG |
@@ -1050,6 +1063,7 @@
 		return 0;
 
 	switch (amdgpu_ip_version(adev, NBIO_HWIP, 0)) {
+	case IP_VERSION(2, 1, 1):
 	case IP_VERSION(2, 3, 0):
 	case IP_VERSION(2, 3, 1):
 	case IP_VERSION(2, 3, 2):
